              <h2 class="h1">Why is using thermal imagery is useful in understanding koala behavior?</h2>
            </header> 
            <p>An infrared camera is able to, using the radiation emitted by objects, calculate the surface temperature of everything in the frame. It's important to note that it can only observe surface temperatures, and not the core temperatures of, for example, large mammals. You can learn more about how thermal cameras work on our Science page.</p>
            <p>In this experiment, researchers were able to use thermal imagery to find the surface temperatures of both the koalas and the trees they hug.</p>
