              <h2 class="h1">The Experiment</h2>
            </header>
            <p>Researchers tracked koalas in summer and winter. For each data point, they recorded koala posture and tree species, along with the air and tree temperatures within 0.5 meters of the koala. They also took a picture of each koala with a thermal camera, to obtain the koala's and tree's temperatures.</p>
            <p>With this data, researchers could then use an energy (heat) budget model to estimate how much heat koalas can lose when tree-hugging.</p>
